1251C 101st Legislative Session 1251
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1251
AMENDME NT 1251C
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Mulder
This bill has been extensively amended (hoghoused) and may no longer be consistent with the original
intention of the sponsor.
1 An Act to create the community-based providers methodology supplement fund,
2 create the target teacher salary supplement fund, and provide for the transfer
3 of certain unobligated cash balances to the funds.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
5 Section 1. That § 4-7-31 be AMENDED:
6 4-7-31. There is hereby established within the state treasury the budget reserve
7 fund. Expenditures from the fund may occur only by special appropriation of the
8 Legislature and may redress only unforeseen expenditure obligations or unforeseen
9 revenue shortfalls, as may constitute an emergency pursuant to S.D. Const., Art. III, § 1.
10 Section 2. That § 4-7-32 be AMENDED:
11 4-7-32. The transfer of all prior year unobligated cash must occur in accordance
12 with this section:
13 (1) On July first of each fiscal year or at such the time that the prior fiscal year general
14 fund ending unobligated cash balance is determined, the commissioner of the
15 Bureau of Finance and Management shall transfer all prior year unobligated cash,
16 up to an amount equal to equaling ten percent of the general fund appropriations
17 from the general appropriation act for the prior fiscal year, into the budget reserve
18 fund. In no event shall the The cash balance in the budget reserve fund be greater
19 than may not exceed ten percent of the general fund appropriations from the
20 general appropriation act for the prior fiscal year.
21 Expenditures out of the budget reserve fund shall only be by special appropriation of the
22 Legislature and shall only redress such unforeseen expenditure obligations or such
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1251C 2 1251
1 unforeseen revenue shortfalls as may constitute an emergency pursuant to S.D.
2 Const., Art. III, § 1.; and
3 (2) If any unobligated cash balance remains after the requirements of subdivision (1)
4 are met, the commissioner must transfer:
5 (a) Thirty percent of the remaining balance to the community-based providers
6 methodology supplement fund, created in section 4 of this Act;
7 (b) Thirty percent of the remaining balance to the target teacher salary
8 supplement fund, created in section 3 of this Act; and
9 (c) Forty percent of the remaining balance to the general revenue replacement
10 fund, created in § 4-7-45.
11 Section 3. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 13-13:
12 There is created in the state treasury the target teacher salary supplement fund.
13 The fund consists of moneys specified for deposit in the fund pursuant to § 4-7-32. The
14 Department of Education shall administer the fund. The purpose of the fund is to enable
15 an increase to the target teacher salary, as set forth in § 13-13-10.1.
16 The department, as part of the annual budget submission, in accordance with § 4-
17 7-7, shall submit a budget request utilizing money from the fund to provide an increase
18 in the target teacher salary, as set forth in § 13-13-10.1.
19 Interest on moneys credited to the fund must remain in the fund.
20 Expenditures from the fund must be budgeted through the general appropriation
21 bill.
22 Section 4. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 28-22:
23 There is created in the state treasury the community-based providers methodology
24 supplement fund. The fund consists of moneys specified for deposit in the fund pursuant
25 to § 4-7-32. The Department of Human Services and the Department of Social Services
26 shall each administer that portion of the fund to be used by the agency for the purpose of
27 enabling an increase in the rates payable to the types of community-based providers listed
28 in § 28-22-6, in order for the rate methodology of each provider to be closer to one
29 hundred percent of the methodology established in chapter 28-22.
30 Each department, as part of the annual budget submission, in accordance with § 4-
31 7-7, shall submit a budget request utilizing money from the fund to provide a uniform
32 increase in rates for community-based providers and specify the percentage of
33 methodology each community-based provider is to be at with the change.
